criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Adult patients complaining of shortness of breath, with two or more chronic
             non-communicable diseases (patients with comorbidities)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Morbid obesity;

          -  Any chronic diseases in the stage of exacerbation and / or decompensation;

          -  Systemic diseases, cancer;

          -  Cardiac arrhythmias: persistent atrial fibrillation or paroxysmal atrial fibrillation
             with frequent paroxysms;

          -  History of myocardial infarction, stroke, heart failure with reduced ejection
             fraction;

          -  Storage diseases, hypertrophic cardiomyopathy, concentric hypertrophy;

          -  Congenital and acquired heart defect;
